						               													<description>You are part of a colony of intelligent spiders in a secret military research base struggling to survive in a harsh &amp;ldquo;Bug eat Bug&amp;rdquo; world. Build your web, grow your colony and enhance your skills as you struggle to gain food and fend off attackers. There is an ominous humming sound as the Hoover-Bot 3000 gets closer and closer to the web, threatening a to destroy to your colony in a horrible Hoovergeddon. Your only chance is build an EMP (Electro Magnetic Pulse weapon) from parts you find in the lab and fire it off to destroy the Hoover-Bot. Can you build the EMP in time, or will you be overrun by attacking critters and meet your Hoovergeddon.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Description&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Arachnid is a cooperative game for 2-4 players. Each player is a spider with unique abilities controlled by their own action board with upgradable worker placement spots. The center play area is a hex grid, where the spiders reside and tiles are placed as the web is spun. This shared web is the spider&amp;rsquo;s home, where food is trapped, new skills are acquired, and new workers are hatched.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Flies occasionally fly by, becoming trapped, and eventually, food. Players influence when the Flies are triggered, but this also increases the risk of Critters attacking the web. It's a fine balance between starvation and safety. Players can also enhance their spider skills, but this involves sacrificing parts of their valuable web home.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to lose&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-If the web somehow becomes detached from the edges of the board due to critter attacks, it will mean the end of the colony.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-if the Golden Scarab reached the Den in the center of the web , then &amp;quot;Activates&amp;quot;, the colony will be destroyed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-If the the Hoover-Bot reaches the web, the game will end in a horrible Hoovergeddon.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to win&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Find enough spare parts to create the EMP, then all spiders meet at the Den to set it off and fry the Hoover-Bot. Easy as Pie!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
